Children carry the spirit of Armenian light, Stepanakert, Karabakh, 1992; photo by Aram Ohanian.“These kids survived Azeri rocket bombardments targeting civilians in the winter and spring of 1992”, says Aram Ohanian, a Yerevan citizen who took this photo while traveling with American journalists in Armenia and Karabakh. Courtesy of Aram Ohanian.
1992; 2016 calendar; Armenian; Karabagh; Republic of Armenia; Stepanakert; boys; children; war;
Featured in Project SAVE's 2016 Calendar, Armenians Beyond the 100th…Our Children Carry the Light

Armenian Red Cross volunteers, "Garmeer Khach", Whitinsville, Massachusetts, c. 1918;
photographer unknown.
Women display the Red Cross banner inscribed in Armenian with initials for the Armenian Revolutionary Federation and the words “Red Cross Women’s Society;” the flag of the first Armenian Republic, which used sky blue for the middle stripe and thus appears white; and the United States Stars and Stripes.

Purchased from an Armenian family's estate sale, name date location photographer are unknown.
Courtesy of Armena Andranian
